ğŸ”¹ 1. Introduction

This project is a Console-Based Online Banking System developed using Core Java (OOP).
It allows a user to create bank accounts, log in, check balance, deposit money, withdraw money, transfer funds between accounts, and close accounts.
All banking data is stored in Java collections (HashMap).

ğŸ”¹ 2. Project Objective

The main goal is to simulate real banking operations in a simple manner:

Create a secure user account

Authenticate using a password

Perform financial operations safely

Prevent invalid or dangerous transactions

ğŸ”¹ 3. System Architecture

The project uses three core components:

âœ”ï¸ (A) UI / Controller Layer

Runs inside main() menu

Takes user input from console

Dispatches actions to Bank

âœ”ï¸ (B) Business Logic Layer â€” Bank Class

Manages accounts

Validates input

Executes operations (deposit, withdraw, transfer)

Stores accounts using a HashMap

âœ”ï¸ (C) Data Layer â€” Account Class

Stores account details

Encapsulates balance

Protects password

Offers functions to change account state

ğŸ”¹ 4. Core Features & Implementation
â­ 1. Account Creation

User enters name + password

System generates unique account ID

Stored in HashMap

â­ 2. User Authentication

When logging in, password is compared

Only valid accounts are allowed

â­ 3. Balance Inquiry

The account shows current balance

â­ 4. Deposit

Adds amount to account balance

Blocks negative values

â­ 5. Withdraw

Deducts money only if balance is enough

